Guy T. HELVERING, Commissioner of Internal Revenue, v. Daisy Christine PATTERSON, Executrix of the Estate of Frank H. Patterson, Deceased. No. 1794. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit Oct. 18, 1938. James W. Morris, Asst. Atty. Gen., and J. P. Wenchel, Chief Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. Albert F. Plillix, of Kansas City, Mo., for petitioner.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.-

PER CURIAM.

Petition for review dismissed on motion of petitioner.
